		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Principality of Andorra is a landlocked micro-state located on the Iberian Peninsula, with France to its North, and Spain to its South. It is the sixth smallest country in Europe with a size a little more than two times that of Washington D.C. Early human Archaeological discoveries in Andorra go back 9500 years. Around the year 600 BC, the area was inhabited by Iberians. The area came under the influence of the Visigoths for a couple hundred years during which time Christianity spread. When the Muslim Empire conquered most of the Iberian Peninsula, Andorrans were protected by the Franks. Charlemagne, the king of the Franks, gave the Andorrans's soldiers to fight the Muslim Moors and keep them from entering France. In return, he gave them special rights.
   
Andorra had several rulers beginning with Charlemagne’s grandson. It was handed over to many rulers either through marriage or as a gift through the centuries. In 1278, there was a dispute about whether Andorra belonged to the bishop of Urgell in Catalonia, or the count of Foix, ultimately of France. The conflict was resolved and the First Paréage of Andorra was signed, accepting a shared sovereignty.
			</p>
