				Today, Andorra is the only co-principality in the world, called “diarchy” run together by the bishop of Urgell in Catalonia (Spain), and the president of France. The people of Andorra are of Catalan descent, and the official language is Catalan, a Romance language derived from Latin. However, Spanish, Portuguese, and French are also commonly spoken.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
